{"type":"message","id":"c5325889","parentId":"e799753c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:38:51.638Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9z6wcr419kbu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 153820\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and figure out what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. They've done architecture cross-analysis, gap-decay synthesis, LLM-augmented pulse\r\n3. Most importantly, they've done a CFI Compression Experiment and found:\r\n   - CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is too aggressive\r\n   - Constant format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n   - Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should run this experiment. But first, I need to understand what's already in place. Let me check what files exist from the previous experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the user wants me to advance the goals. The pending task is clear: implement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nBut I don't have access to the pulse data or the previous experiment files. The previous experiment result is in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. \r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. First check what data exists\r\n2. Design the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n3. Implement it\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files might be available. The user mentioned:\r\n\r\n\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\r\n\r\nI'll need to create a hybrid scoring script that tests the proposed formula against binary thresholds. The script should compare the new approach with existing methods to validate the scoring technique. I'll focus on designing an experiment that demonstrates the effectiveness of the CFI×Freq hybrid scoring method.\r\n\r\nThe experiment requires precise data extraction and comparison. I'll develop a Python script to parse existing token data, calculate the hybrid score, and generate comparative metrics. Key steps include filtering tokens, applying the scoring formula, and analyzing performance across different token sets.\r\n\r\nThe experiment design document will outline the specific hypothesis, methodology, and expected outcomes. I'll structure it to clearly explain how the hybrid scoring approach might improve token evaluation compared to binary threshold methods.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the key insight: constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) need to be distinguished from true research trajectory tokens. The next step is to implement and document the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experiment design document for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring test, specifying the formula, expected outcomes, and methodology to validate whether this approach distinguishes metaprogramming artifacts from genuine causal tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n**Formula:** `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`\r\n\r\nThis hybrid score should:\r\n- **Suppress constant-format tokens** (freq≈160, CFI=1): score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (BUT capped at min(1, 160/120) = 1.0, so score = 1.0)\r\n  - Wait—this still gives score=1.0 for constant tokens!\r\n\r\n**Revised formula needed:**\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × (freq(T)/120)  # raw product\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen constant-format: score = 1.0 × (160/120) = 1.33 (over threshold!)\r\nResearch trajectory: score = 0.5 × (50/120) = 0.21 (under threshold)\r\n\r\nThis SHOULD distinguish them.\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcomes\r\n\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score | Decision |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|----------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.33 | ❌ EXCLUDE (>1.0) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.33 | ❌ EXCLUDE |\r\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.33 | ❌ EXCLUDE |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 1.09 | ❌ EXCLUDE (still too high) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 80 | 0.65 | 0.43 | ✅ INCLUDE |\r\n| \"compression\" | 45 | 0.58 | 0.22 | ✅ INCLUDE |\r\n| \"temporal\" | 30 | 0.45 | 0.11 | ❌ EXCLUDE (<0.15 threshold) |\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- 200 pulses from `pulse_archive/`\r\n- 80/20 train/test split (160/40)\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Precision**: % of selected tokens that are true research concepts\r\n- **Recall**: % of true research concepts captured\r\n- **F1**: Harmonic mean\r\n\r\n### Comparison Baselines\r\n1. Binary CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 (from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\r\n2. Binary CFI ≥ 0.5 AND\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:38:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381131636}}
